I see the issue! Looking at the API response, most models have `model_picker_enabled: false`, and in the `discover_models_from_api` function (lines 206-210), we filter out models where `model_picker_enabled == false`:

```rust
// Skip models explicitly disabled in the picker
if model.model_picker_enabled == Some(false) {
    return false;
}
```

Only `gpt-4o` has `model_picker_enabled: true`, so only 1 model passes the filter.

This is the wrong behavior - `model_picker_enabled` refers to whether the model should show up in GitHub's own UI picker, not whether it's available for API use. The API returns all these models because they ARE available for use, they just aren't the "primary" model shown in the UI.

We should not filter based on `model_picker_enabled`. Instead, we should just filter out models that are explicitly disabled via the `policy.state == "disabled"` check, which is already there.

